node.text: We had a blast in Jamaica and we can’t wait to do it again. As promised, I uploaded a full review of the resort we stayed in, and I just dropped an entire vlog on YouTube of our stay in Jamaica. Head to my website at thatnursecooks.com to check it out!!! Link in bio!!

So I got up this morning to get the kids ready and realized I forgot to buy milk last night 😱 Then I remembered the instant porridges that the lovely team at @gracefoods gave to me and I thought well they can eat this! It was their first time trying it and they loved it! You know I always make porridge for them so if they liked this, then it must be really good! Definitely adding this to my list of quick breakfasts for those school mornings when I’m short on time! .

node.text: We had a blast in Jamaica. We always do! We’ve been home for over a week now and while it was sooo good to get away, we’re happy & grateful to be home safely. With that in mind, I want to make sure that I get this message across. Please travel safely! I get it. We all have made sacrifices and I do believe that people should be free to make their own decisions but those decisions should not jeopardize the health of others. I know not everyone who follows me lives in the USA and are not bound by our mandates and laws but the truth remains the same no matter which country you come from. Make the decisions that are right for you and your family and prioritize your safety! Obey your local laws, and adhere to the guidelines set forth by the experts that are trying to keep you safe. People travel for more than one reason and they need to be equipped with the information to do so safely. Even if you’ve been on the fence about travelling, save the information that I’ve shared so that when you are ready and feel comfortable enough to travel, you have the right information. Head over to my IG story right now! I created a sticker for you guys to drop all of your questions that you may have. Reminder: please keep it respectful! You don’t have to agree with someone’s choice in order to be respectful and it cost you nothing to be nice! Wash your hands, wear your mask, and take care of yourself!

node.text:
How did we spend our lockdown day? Safety is of the utmost importance so we followed the rules by staying put on our resort. Honestly after doing a bunch of activities and trying to cram everything in on those days where movement was allowed, we welcomed a day of rest! We slept in for the first time in months (lol), spent the whole day reconnecting and planning our future, @samsaralegendsnegril scheduled a nice couples massage and made sure we were greeted with fresh coconut water, and we had a nice sunset dinner on the cliffs! No matter how or when you plan your trip, find ways to be creative by partaking in resort activities or if you’re like us, chill with your bae and just be♥️
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Redefining farm to table on Booby Cay Island. @samsaralegendsnegril organized a day trip for us to get some grilled lobster. Watching your lobster come fresh from the ocean and tossed right onto the grill. Topped with melted butter with onion, garlic, tomatoes, and peppers and toasted garlic hardo bread. The experience was amazing. 🔥

node.text:
There’s a lot of misinformation circulating around regarding Jamaica’s lockdown protocols! Don’t cancel your travel plans, I promise you, Jamaica is a safe place to visit. I’d recommend that you travel Tuesday to Saturday or Wednesday to Monday. Get the most out of those days when you’re free to do as you please and trust me, if a non movement day falls on your last day you’re going to be wiped out from all the activities you’re going to want to stay on your resort to relax anyway! Lastly, always make sure to follow @visitjamaica and go to visitjamaica.com to complete your travel authorization and get all the info you need. @andrewholnessjm ‘s twitter account also gives live updates on when the non-movement days are occuring as well.
.
.
.
.
.
